
This set of tests is similar to the smoke tests in the smoke directory. 

Files Makefile.defs and Makefile.rules should be used in individual test Makefiles.

N.B. The TESTNAME in case of a multisource test must be different from names of individual test source files. Otherwise make will be confused.

Example of individual Makefile:
include ../../Makefile.defs

TESTNAME       = vmulsum
TESTSRC_MAIN   = main.c
TESTSRC_AUX    = vmul.c vsum.c
TESTSRC_ALL    = $(TESTSRC_MAIN) $(TESTSRC_AUX)

CLANG          = clang
OMP_BIN        = $(AOMP)/bin/$(CLANG)
CC             = $(OMP_BIN) $(VERBOSE)
#-ccc-print-phases
#"-\#\#\#"

include ../Makefile.rules
